definitions.definition: A nocturnal insectivorous bird of North America ( Antrostomus vociferus , syn. Caprimulgus vociferus ), a type of nightjar , named after its characteristic call.
The distinctive call of the above bird.
examples: The bird sang his whippoorwills all night.
